  "writeup": "The biggest story dominating Bills news on June 28, 2026 is the organization's decision to exclude O.J. Simpson from the Wall of Fame at the new Highmark Stadium, a move that has sparked fierce debate among fans and media alike. Reactions range from praise for the decision to sharp criticism, with some arguing the Bills are 'erasing history' while others applaud the stance given Simpson's controversial legacy. On the football side, Josh Allen is singing the praises of new wide receiver DJ Moore and new quarterbacks coach Bo Hardegree, though ESPN's ranking of the Bills' offensive playmaker group near the bottom of the NFL is raising eyebrows. Contract extension discussions for guard O'Cyrus Torrence and tight end Dalton Kincaid are also heating up, while ticket prices for the new stadium are drawing complaints from fans calling them 'outrageous.'",
